        15092
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        15094,
        15184
      ],
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Delete Data Source<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation removes a data source from your Azure Search service."
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>NOTE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> If any indexers reference the data source that you're deleting, the delete operation will still proceed.",
      "pos": [
        15321,
        15434
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, those indexers will transition into an error state upon their next run.",
      "pos": [
        15435,
        15515
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        15521,
        15529
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Status Code: 204 No Content is returned for a successful response.",
      "pos": [
        15533,
        15599
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexer Operations",
      "pos": [
        15604,
        15622
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An indexer is the resource that connects data sources with target search indexes.",
      "pos": [
        15624,
        15705
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You should plan on creating one indexer for every target index and data source combination.",
      "pos": [
        15706,
        15797
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can have multiple indexers writing into the same index.",
      "pos": [
        15798,
        15857
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, an indexer can only write into a single index.",
      "pos": [
        15858,
        15913
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can create and manage indexers via simple HTTP requests (POST, GET, PUT, DELETE) against a given indexer resource.",
      "pos": [
        15916,
        16034
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After creating an indexer, you can retrieve its execution status using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Get Indexer Status<ept id=\"p1\">](#GetIndexerStatus)</ept> operation.",
      "pos": [
        16037,
        16162
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also run an indexer at any time (instead of or in addition to running it periodically on a schedule) using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Run Indexer<ept id=\"p1\">](#RunIndexer)</ept> operation.",
      "pos": [
        16163,
        16319
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create Indexer",
      "pos": [
        16325,
        16339
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can create a new indexer within an Azure Search service using an HTTP POST request.",
      "pos": [
        16341,
        16428
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Alternatively, you can use PUT and specify the data source name on the URI.",
      "pos": [
        16581,
        16656
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the data source does not exist, it will be created.",
      "pos": [
        16657,
        16711
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: The maximum number of indexers allowed varies by pricing tier.",
      "pos": [
        16814,
        16886
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The free service allows up to 3 indexers.",
      "pos": [
        16887,
        16928
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Standard service allows 50 indexers.",
      "pos": [
        16929,
        16965
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Request Body Syntax<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        17009,
        17032
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The body of the request contains an indexer definition, which specifies the data source and the target index for indexing, as well as optional indexing schedule and parameters.",
      "pos": [
        17034,
        17210
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The syntax for structuring the request payload is as follows.",
      "pos": [
        17214,
        17275
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A sample request is provided further on in this topic.",
      "pos": [
        17276,
        17330
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexing Schedule",
      "pos": [
        17773,
        17790
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An indexer can optionally specify a schedule.",
      "pos": [
        17794,
        17839
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If a schedule is present, the indexer will run periodically as per schedule.",
      "pos": [
        17840,
        17916
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Schedule has the following attributes:",
      "pos": [
        17917,
        17955
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`interval`</ph>: Required.",
      "pos": [
        17959,
        17980
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A duration value that specifies an interval or period for indexer runs.",
      "pos": [
        17981,
        18052
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The smallest allowed interval is 5 minutes; the longest is one day.",
      "pos": [
        18053,
        18120
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It must be formatted as an XSD \"dayTimeDuration\" value (a restricted subset of an <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ISO 8601 duration<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/#dayTimeDuration)</ept> value).",
      "pos": [
        18121,
        18283
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The pattern for this is: <ph id=\"ph1\">`P(nD)(T(nH)(nM))`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        18284,
        18328
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Examples: <ph id=\"ph1\">`PT15M`</ph> for every 15 minutes, <ph id=\"ph2\">`PT2H`</ph> for every 2 hours.",
      "pos": [
        18329,
        18394
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`startTime`</ph>: Required.",
      "pos": [
        18399,
        18421
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An UTC datetime when the indexer should start running.",
      "pos": [
        18422,
        18476
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexing Parameters",
      "pos": [
        18481,
        18500
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An indexer can optionally specify several parameters that affect its behavior.",
      "pos": [
        18504,
        18582
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All of the parameters are optional.",
      "pos": [
        18583,
        18618
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`maxFailedItems`</ph> : The number of items that can fail to be indexed before an indexer run is considered as failure.",
      "pos": [
        18624,
        18738
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Default is <ph id=\"ph1\">`0`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        18739,
        18754
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Information about failed items is returned by the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Get Indexer Status<ept id=\"p1\">](#GetIndexerStatus)</ept> operation.",
      "pos": [
        18755,
        18855
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`maxFailedItemsPerBatch`</ph> : The number of items that can fail to be indexed in each batch before an indexer run is considered as failure.",
      "pos": [
        18860,
        18996
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Default is <ph id=\"ph1\">`0`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        18997,
        19012
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`base64EncodeKeys`</ph>: Specifies whether or not document keys will be base-64 encoded.",
      "pos": [
        19016,
        19099
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure Search imposes restrictions on characters that can be present in a document key.",
      "pos": [
        19100,
        19186
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, the values in your source data may contain characters that are invalid.",
      "pos": [
        19187,
        19267
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If it is necessary to index such values as document keys, this flag can be set to true.",
      "pos": [
        19268,
        19355
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Default is <ph id=\"ph1\">`false`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        19356,
        19375
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Request Body Examples<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        19421,
        19446
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following example creates an indexer that copies data from the table referenced by the <ph id=\"ph1\">`ordersds`</ph> data source to the <ph id=\"ph2\">`orders`</ph> index on a schedule that starts on Jan 1, 2015 UTC and runs hourly.",
      "pos": [
        19448,
        19645
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each indexer invocation will be successful if no more than 5 items fail to be indexed in each batch, and no more than 10 items fail to be indexed in total.",
      "pos": [
        19646,
        19801
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        20158,
        20166
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "201 Created for a successful request.",
      "pos": [
        20170,
        20207
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Update Indexer",
      "pos": [
        20213,
        20227
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can update an existing indexer using an HTTP PUT request.",
      "pos": [
        20229,
        20290
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You specify the name of the indexer to update on the request URI:",
      "pos": [
        20291,
        20356
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Request",
      "pos": [
        20521,
        20528
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        20532,
        20630
      ],
      "content": "The request body syntax is the same as for <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create Indexer requests<ept id=\"p1\">](#CreateIndexerRequestSyntax)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        20634,
        20642
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a successful request: 201 Created if a new indexer was created, and 204 No Content if an existing indexer was updated.",
      "pos": [
        20646,
        20768
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "List Indexers",
      "pos": [
        20774,
