      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Get Indexer",
      "pos": [
        21794,
        21805
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        21807,
        21883
      ],
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get Indexer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation gets the indexer definition from Azure Search."
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        22013,
        22021
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Status Code: 200 OK is returned for a successful response.",
      "pos": [
        22025,
        22083
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        22085,
        22189
      ],
      "content": "The response is similar to examples in <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create Indexer example requests<ept id=\"p1\">](#CreateIndexerRequestExamples)</ept>:"
    },
    {
      "content": "Delete Indexer",
      "pos": [
        22548,
        22562
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        22564,
        22647
      ],
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Delete Indexer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation removes an indexer from your Azure Search service."
    },
    {
      "content": "When an indexer is deleted, the indexer executions in progress at that time will run to completion, but no further executions will be scheduled.",
      "pos": [
        22778,
        22922
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Attempts to use a non-existent indexer will result in HTTP status code 404 Not Found.",
      "pos": [
        22923,
        23008
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        23014,
        23022
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Status Code: 204 No Content is returned for a successful response.",
      "pos": [
        23026,
        23092
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Run Indexer",
      "pos": [
        23124,
        23135
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        23137,
        23263
      ],
      "content": "In addition to running periodically on a schedule, an indexer can also be invoked on demand via the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Run Indexer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation:"
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        23399,
        23407
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Status Code: 202 Accepted is returned for a successful response.",
      "pos": [
        23411,
        23475
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Get Indexer Status",
      "pos": [
        23513,
        23531
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        23533,
        23635
      ],
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get Indexer Status<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation retrieves the current status and execution history of an indexer:"
    },
    {
      "content": "Response",
      "pos": [
        23773,
        23781
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Status Code: 200 OK for a successful response.",
      "pos": [
        23785,
        23831
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The response body contains information about overall indexer health status, the last indexer invocation, as well as the history of recent indexer invocations (if present).",
      "pos": [
        23833,
        24004
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A sample response body looks like this:",
      "pos": [
        24007,
        24046
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexer Status",
      "pos": [
        24836,
        24850
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexer status can be one of the following  values:",
      "pos": [
        24854,
        24905
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`running`</ph> indicates that the indexer is running normally.",
      "pos": [
        24909,
        24966
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that some of the indexer executions may still be failing, so it's a good idea to check the <ph id=\"ph1\">`lastResult`</ph> property as well.",
      "pos": [
        24967,
        25093
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`error`</ph> indicates that the indexer experienced an error that cannot be corrected without human intervention.",
      "pos": [
        25098,
        25206
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, the data source credentials may have expired, or the schema of the data source or of the target index has changed in a breaking way.",
      "pos": [
        25207,
        25352
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexer Execution Result",
      "pos": [
        25357,
        25381
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An indexer execution result contains information about a single indexer execution.",
      "pos": [
        25385,
        25467
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The latest result is surfaced as the <ph id=\"ph1\">`lastResult`</ph> property of the indexer status.",
      "pos": [
        25468,
        25549
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Other recent results, if present, are returned as the <ph id=\"ph1\">`executionHistory`</ph> property of the indexer status.",
      "pos": [
        25550,
        25654
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexer execution result contains the following properties:",
      "pos": [
        25657,
        25716
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`status`</ph>: the status of this execution.",
      "pos": [
        25721,
        25760
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Indexer Execution Status<ept id=\"p1\">](#IndexerExecutionStatus)</ept> below for details.",
      "pos": [
        25761,
        25835
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        25840,
        25893
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`errorMessage`</ph>: error message for a failed execution."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        25898,
        25959
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`startTime`</ph>: the time in UTC when this execution has started."
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`endTime`</ph>: the time in UTC when this execution has ended.",
      "pos": [
        25963,
        26020
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This value is not set if the execution is still in progress.",
      "pos": [
        26021,
        26081
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        26085,
        26131
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`errors`</ph>: a list of item-level errors, if any."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        26136,
        26270
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`itemsProcessed`</ph>: the number of data source items (for example, table rows) that the indexer attempted to index during this execution."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        26275,
        26344
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`itemsFailed`</ph>: the number of items that failed during this execution."
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`initialTrackingState`</ph>: always <ph id=\"ph2\">`null`</ph> for the first indexer execution, or if the data change tracking policy is not enabled on the data source used.",
      "pos": [
        26351,
        26499
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If such a policy is enabled, in subsequent executions this value indicates the first (lowest) change tracking value processed by this execution.",
      "pos": [
        26500,
        26644
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`finalTrackingState`</ph>: always <ph id=\"ph2\">`null`</ph> if the data change tracking policy is not enabled on the data source used.",
      "pos": [
        26649,
        26759
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Otherwise, indicates the latest (highest) change tracking value successfully processed by this execution.",
      "pos": [
        26760,
        26865
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Indexer Execution Status<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>",
      "pos": [
        26906,
        26934
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexer execution status captures the status of a single indexer execution.",
      "pos": [
        26936,
        27011
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It can have the following values:",
      "pos": [
        27012,
        27045
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        27049,
        27123
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`success`</ph> indicates that the indexer execution has completed successfully."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        27127,
        27192
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`inProgress`</ph> indicates that the indexer execution is in progress."
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`transientFailure`</ph> indicates that the indexer invocation has failed, but the failure may be transient.",
      "pos": [
        27197,
        27299
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Indexer invocations will continue per schedule, if one is present.",
      "pos": [
        27300,
        27366
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`persistentFailure`</ph> indicates that the indexer has failed in a way that likely requires human intervention (for example, because of a schema incompatibility between the data source and the target index).",
      "pos": [
        27371,
        27574
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Scheduled indexer executions stop; user action is required to address the issue (described in the <ph id=\"ph1\">`errorMessage`</ph> property) and restart indexer execution.",
      "pos": [
        27575,
        27728
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        27733,
        27826
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">`reset`</ph> indicates that the indexer has been reset by a call to Reset Indexer API (see below)."
    },
    {
      "content": "Reset Indexer",
      "pos": [
        27861,
        27874
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Reset Indexer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> operation resets the change tracking state associated with the indexer.",
      "pos": [
        27876,
        27969
      ]
    },
    {
